nodes.title: Reference Images
widgets_values:
These images are only used to extract the open pose. They have no weight to how the video actually looks.

The Upscale Image node is optional and only there to ensure everything has the same size

nodes.title: Keyframes
widgets_values: For the middle keyframes, we need two interpolations: one to go to the keyframe, and one to move away from it.

nodes.title: Keyframes
widgets_values: For the end keyframes, we end on the last keyframe with a strength of 1.0. Change batch_index_to_end to a widget if you don't want to end the pose on the last frame.

nodes.title: Number of Frames
widgets_values: This is the total frames the final video will have. We also end the last keyframe on this value.

nodes.title: Image Size
widgets_values: Use this to keep the start and end poses the same size as the output.

nodes.title: Prepend text
widgets_values: RAW photo of business woman, blazer jacket
nude, nsfw, canvas frame, cartoon, 3d, out-of-frame, ugly, cross-eyed, embedding:JuggernautNegative-neg

nodes.title: CLIP Positive Prompt Traveling
widgets_values: highly detailed, realistic, portrait, simple background, turtleneck sweater

nodes.title: Keyframes
widgets_values: For the starting keyframe, we start at 0 with a strength of 1.0 to the keyframe we want to stop using this pose with a weak strength like 0.2.

nodes.title: Prompt Traveling
widgets_values: Use the prompt traveling to change the prompt as the frames moves.  Use the prepend & append text for parts of the prompt that should stay the same for the whole generation.

nodes.title: Need More Keyframes?
widgets_values: Copy and paste this middle group.  The most important part is to update the batch_index in the interpolation nodes!

nodes.title: Reference Images
widgets_values: If have open pose images, you can bypass the preprocessor and put the image in directly.  If you don't have DW Preprocessor, you can use the Open Pose Preprocessor one instead

nodes.title: Reference Images
widgets_values: There's no need for the reference images to be of the same subject, we only want the pose.

nodes.title: Uniform Context Options
widgets_values:
Useful for making animations longer than 16 frames.

Set closed_loop to true if you want an endless looping animation (longer rendering times). Be sure to also set the last control net image to be the same as the first if you want that.

nodes.title: Generating your keyframes
widgets_values:
This group is entirely optional.

You can use enable this to generate some images to feed into the open pose.  Be sure to bypass the animatediff generation as you do this.


Leave this as bypass when doing the main flow.
